'''''Star Wars Insider'' 44''' is the forty-fourth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[June]]/[[July]] [[1999]]. The [[Wikipedia:Barcode|barcode]] on the cover mislabeled this issue as [[Star Wars Insider 39|issue 39]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe]]: [[Silas Carson]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[Prequel Profile]]: [[Peter Walpole]]"
*"[[Bookshelf|''Star Wars'' Book Shelf]]" &ndash; Episode I Books: Let the Invasion Begin {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; Bootlegs from Jabba's Court? {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[Pernilla August: Universal Mother]]" {{C|by [[Annika Gustafsson]]}}
*:<small>What's it like when your baby grows up to be [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]]? It probably wasn't the fate [[Shmi Skywalker Lars/Legends|Shmi Skywalker]] imagined for Anakin. Annika Gustafsson talks to Sweden's Pernilla August about bringing [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] most important mother to life.</small>
*"[[John Williams: Score of Force]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Indiana Jones, ''E.T.'', ''Superman'', ''Jurassic Park'', ''Jaws'', and the ''Star Wars'' saga—how did all of this memorable music come from the mind of one man? The ''Insider'' talks to composer John Williams about his return to the ''Star Wars'' universe for Episode I [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']].</small>
*"[[Ships of Episode I]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>What's a new ''Star Wars'' movie without a new fleet of starships? [[Daniel Wallace]] introduces us to the dizzying new universe of ''Phantom Menace'' ships—from [[Podracer/Legends|Podracers]] to [[Consular-class light cruiser/Legends|Republic Cruisers]], they're all here! Features exclusive photos from Episode I!</small>
*"[[Natalie Portman: All Hail the Queen]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>[[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Amidala]], Natalie Portman reigns supreme over the new ''Star Wars'' film. Luckily, she's more than up to the challenge. [[Scott Chernoff]] talks to the young woman who's got the whole universe in her hands.</small>

